# DevLog 020 – Interactive Music Review

Today focused on reviewing the interactive music implementation rather than expanding it.

The review covered the complete Unity and Wwise architecture, including MusicManager, State Groups, Playlist Containers, Music Segments, Events, and routing.

The system required very few changes, confirming that the architectural decisions made throughout Milestone 2 resulted in a clean and maintainable implementation.

The only modifications were removing an unused Play_MS_Exploration event and renaming the reused exploration music segment inside the PostCombat playlist to better communicate design intent.

The review also confirmed that Unity controls gameplay state while Wwise controls playback logic, keeping responsibilities clearly separated.

Interactive Music implementation is now considered complete for Milestone 2.